default: before_script: - apt-get update - apt-get install unzip - curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/emacs-eask/cli/master/webinstall/install.sh | sh - export PATH=&#34;$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH&#34; test-26.3: image: silex/emacs:26.3-ci script: - eask clean all - eask package - eask install - eask compile test-27.2: image: silex/emacs:27.2-ci script: - eask clean all - eask package - eask install - eask compile test-28.2: image: silex/emacs:28.2-ci script: - eask clean all - eask package - eask install - eask compile test-29.4: image: silex/emacs:29.4-ci script: - eask clean all - eask package - eask install - eask compile test-30.1: image: silex/emacs:30.1-ci script: - eask clean all - eask package - eask install - eask compile This example is testing your Emacs Lisp package in the below environment;
OS Emacs Eask Linux (Debian) 26.x, 27.x, 28.x, 29.x, 30.x, snapshot latest macOS n/a latest Windows n/a latest Note ğŸ’¡ You can generate workflow file via eask generate workflow gitlab, see Commands and options for more information!

